OB:
When I attempt to create a FontRegistry instance for my application using the following code:

```java
com.company.product.MyClass
public void createFontRegistry(){
  FontRegistry fonts = new FontRegistry("com.company.product.fonts");
}
```
I get a MissingResourceException. I have a file named 'fonts.properties' in my 'com/company/product/' folder. However, if I try this instead:

```java
com.company.product.MyClass
public void createFontRegistry(){
  ResourceBundle fonts = ResourceBundle.getBundle("com.company.product.fonts");
}
```
There is no exception. Furthermore, if I create a complete copy of the FontRegistry class in my 'com.company.product' package, then it works. My guess is that it is a bug in the FontRegistry. It attempts to load the font resource bundle, but the FontRegistry's class loader is used to do that (see 'readResourceBundle(String)' FontRegistry method).
